<title>BELGIUM: Solvay had 2.1 bln bfr exceptional gain.</title>
<headline>Solvay had 2.1 bln bfr exceptional gain.</headline>
<dateline>BRUSSELS 1997-02-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>Belgian chemicals and drugs company Solvay SA aid on Thursday it booked 2.1 billion francs in exceptional gains in 1996 after none in 1995.</p>
<p>It said the 1996 exceptional gains were due mainly to the sale of its animal health activities -- on which it expected to book a pre-tax capital gain of $190 million -- but also restructurings such as Austrian unit Hallein and the sale of Brazilian unit Plavinil.</p>
